          <p>Whether you're adding a room, converting a garage, or want zone control throughout your home, a ductless mini split system may be the perfect solution. These versatile systems provide both cooling and heating with efficiency ratings that often exceed traditional HVAC systems.</p>

          <h2>How Ductless Mini Splits Work</h2>
          <p>A ductless mini split system consists of two main components:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Outdoor Unit:</strong> A compact condenser/compressor unit installed outside your home</li>
            <li><strong>Indoor Unit(s):</strong> Wall-mounted or ceiling-mounted air handlers installed in each zone</li>
          </ul>
          <p>The two are connected by a small conduit containing refrigerant lines, power, and drain. No ductwork required—just a 3-inch hole through the wall.</p>

          <h2>Perfect Applications for Ductless Systems</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Room Additions:</strong> Add cooling and heating without extending existing ductwork</li>
            <li><strong>Garage Conversions:</strong> Turn your garage into a comfortable living space</li>
            <li><strong>Sunrooms:</strong> Enjoy your sunroom year-round with efficient climate control</li>
            <li><strong>Home Offices:</strong> Keep your workspace comfortable without cooling the whole house</li>
            <li><strong>Above-Garage Apartments:</strong> Independent climate control for rental or guest spaces</li>
            <li><strong>Older Homes:</strong> Add AC to homes without existing ductwork</li>
            <li><strong>Hot/Cold Rooms:</strong> Supplement central AC in rooms that never seem comfortable</li>
            <li><strong>Multi-Zone Homes:</strong> Create separate comfort zones throughout your home</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Benefits of Ductless Mini Splits</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Energy Efficiency:</strong> SEER ratings up to 30+, far exceeding standard AC systems</li>
            <li><strong>Zoned Comfort:</strong> Control temperature independently in each room</li>
            <li><strong>No Duct Losses:</strong> Ducted systems can lose 25-30% of energy through leaky ductwork</li>
            <li><strong>Easy Installation:</strong> Minimal construction required—usually completed in one day</li>
            <li><strong>Quiet Operation:</strong> Whisper-quiet indoor units with sound levels as low as 19 dB</li>
            <li><strong>Heating and Cooling:</strong> Most units provide both, eliminating the need for separate systems</li>
            <li><strong>Improved Air Quality:</strong> Multi-stage filtration removes dust, allergens, and contaminants</li>
            <li><strong>Compact Design:</strong> Small outdoor units and sleek indoor units preserve your home's appearance</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Brands We Install</h2>
